es.ctfassets.net/2h1qowfuxkq7/1tgddFeo9W0C0UmcMDSeXX/85a74a90b21967cbc8fbb28b4e24e80c/Image1_QNL.jpg?w=2127&h=1188&q=85&fit=pad 2127w","srcWebp":"//images.ctfassets.net/2h1qowfuxkq7/1tgddFeo9W0C0UmcMDSeXX/85a74a90b21967cbc8fbb28b4e24e80c/Image1_QNL.jpg?w=1540&h=860&q=85&fm=webp&fit=pad","srcSetWebp":"//images.ctfassets.net/2h1qowfuxkq7/1tgddFeo9W0C0UmcMDSeXX/85a74a90b21967cbc8fbb28b4e24e80c/Image1_QNL.jpg?w=385&h=215&q=85&fm=webp&fit=pad 385w,\n//images.ctfassets.net/2h1qowfuxkq7/1tgddFeo9W0C0UmcMDSeXX/85a74a90b21967cbc8fbb28b4e24e80c/Image1_QNL.jpg?w=770&h=430&q=85&fm=webp&fit=pad 770w,\n//images.ctfassets.net/2h1qowfuxkq7/1tgddFeo9W0C0UmcMDSeXX/85a74a90b21967cbc8fbb28b4e24e80c/Image1_QNL.jpg?w=1540&h=860&q=85&fm=webp&fit=pad 1540w,\n//images.ctfassets.net/2h1qowfuxkq7/1tgddFeo9W0C0UmcMDSeXX/85a74a90b21967cbc8fbb28b4e24e80c/Image1_QNL.jpg?w=2127&h=1188&q=85&fm=webp&fit=pad 2127w","sizes":"(max-width: 1540px) 100vw, 1540px"}}}]},{"__typename":"ContentfulModuleBodyText","id":"fe138f90-81c8-54e0-aa3d-579dc286835e","text":{"childMarkdownRemark":{"html":"<p>The debate’s speakers were Parag Khanna, an Indian-American CEO, international strategist, and author; Sisonke Msimang, a South African writer whose work focuses on race, gender, and equality; and Medea Benjamin, co-founder of the women-led American grassroots advocacy organization CODEPINK. </p>\n<p>The program also featured bridge-building “connector” Govinda Clayton, moderator Ghida Fakhry, and digital correspondent Nelufar Hedayat, who shared questions and comments from livestream viewers around the world.</p>\n<p>During the debate, Khanna acknowledged globalization’s challenges while arguing “the backlash that we talk about today is not against globalization, but rather the governments that have failed to manage it for the benefit of their societies.”</p>\n<p>Benjamin expressed greater concern, saying, “Globalization gives too much power to big, multinational corporations that destroy local businesses, exacerbate inequalities, crush democratic movements, overturn local regulations, and make decisions that affect the lives of billions of people.”</p>\n<p>Msimang argued that globalization is a “smokescreen,” a polarizing term that muddles and overshadows the true underlying issues. She encouraged people everywhere to take action locally, adding “talking about your hopes and fears is a far better starting point than talking about this abstract thing called ‘globalization.’”</p>"}}},{"__typename":"ContentfulModuleImageGallery","id":"32c5bc90-8f8d-5a25-ab29-7af950d8ecb2","images":[{"caption":null,"image":{"id":"eb755ab9-9145-5929-abec-f5edcffe73d2","title":"Image3 DD in Scotland","file":{"details":{"image":{"width":2345,"height":1561}}},"sizes":{"aspectRatio":1.8666666666666667,"src":"//images.ctfassets.net/2h1qowfuxkq7/45X3JIBN7efl3B4u9NmQiT/8d20ce07cc4e8b01ad262ad6a6bb2142/Image3_DD_in_Scotland.jpg?w=1120&h=600&q=85","srcSet":"//images.ctfassets.net/2h1qowfuxkq7/45X3JIBN7efl3B4u9NmQiT/8d20ce07cc4e8b01ad262ad6a6bb2142/Image3_DD_in_Scotland.jpg?w=280&h=150&q=85 280w,\n//images.ctfassets.net/2h1qowfuxkq7/45X3JIBN7efl3B4u9NmQiT/8d20ce07cc4e8b01ad262ad6a6bb2142/Image3_DD_in_Scotland.jpg?w=560&h=300&q=85 560w,\n//images.ctfassets.net/2h1qowfuxkq7/45X3JIBN7efl3B4u9NmQiT/8d20ce07cc4e8b01ad262ad6a6bb2142/Image3_DD_in_Scotland.jpg?w=1120&h=600&q=85 1120w,\n//images.ctfassets.net/2h1qowfuxkq7/45X3JIBN7efl3B4u9NmQiT/8d20ce07cc4e8b01ad262ad6a6bb2142/Image3_DD_in_Scotland.jpg?w=1680&h=900&q=85 1680w,\n//images.ctfassets.net/2h1qowfuxkq7/45X3JIBN7efl3B4u9NmQiT/8d20ce07cc4e8b01ad262ad6a6bb2142/Image3_DD_in_Scotland.jpg?w=2240&h=1200&q=85 2240w,\n//images.ctfassets.net/2h1qowfuxkq7/45X3JIBN7efl3B4u9NmQiT/8d20ce07cc4e8b01ad262ad6a6bb2142/Image3_DD_in_Scotland.jpg?w=2345&h=1256&q=85 2345w","srcWebp":"//images.ctfassets.net/2h1qowfuxkq7/45X3JIBN7efl3B4u9NmQiT/8d20ce07cc4e8b01ad262ad6a6bb2142/Image3_DD_in_Scotland.jpg?w=1120&h=600&q=85&fm=webp","srcSetWebp":"//images.ctfassets.net/2h1qowfuxkq7/45