otland.jpg?w=1540&h=860&q=85&fm=webp&fit=pad","srcSetWebp":"//images.ctfassets.net/2h1qowfuxkq7/45X3JIBN7efl3B4u9NmQiT/8d20ce07cc4e8b01ad262ad6a6bb2142/Image3_DD_in_Scotland.jpg?w=385&h=215&q=85&fm=webp&fit=pad 385w,\n//images.ctfassets.net/2h1qowfuxkq7/45X3JIBN7efl3B4u9NmQiT/8d20ce07cc4e8b01ad262ad6a6bb2142/Image3_DD_in_Scotland.jpg?w=770&h=430&q=85&fm=webp&fit=pad 770w,\n//images.ctfassets.net/2h1qowfuxkq7/45X3JIBN7efl3B4u9NmQiT/8d20ce07cc4e8b01ad262ad6a6bb2142/Image3_DD_in_Scotland.jpg?w=1540&h=860&q=85&fm=webp&fit=pad 1540w,\n//images.ctfassets.net/2h1qowfuxkq7/45X3JIBN7efl3B4u9NmQiT/8d20ce07cc4e8b01ad262ad6a6bb2142/Image3_DD_in_Scotland.jpg?w=2310&h=1290&q=85&fm=webp&fit=pad 2310w,\n//images.ctfassets.net/2h1qowfuxkq7/45X3JIBN7efl3B4u9NmQiT/8d20ce07cc4e8b01ad262ad6a6bb2142/Image3_DD_in_Scotland.jpg?w=2345&h=1310&q=85&fm=webp&fit=pad 2345w","sizes":"(max-width: 1540px) 100vw, 1540px"}}}]},{"__typename":"ContentfulModuleBodyText","id":"ee464034-b663-5799-8820-24297556818b","text":{"childMarkdownRemark":{"html":"<p>The debate’s in-person and online audiences voted twice on key globalization questions.</p>\n<p>During the first vote, Msimang’s position, ‘Make it concrete, not abstract. Stand up’, was the clear winner, with 41.35% of the audience’s votes. Benjamin’s position, ‘Think globally and act locally’, and Khanna’s position, ‘Globalization doesn’t fail. We do’, came in at 29.48% and 29.27% respectively. </p>\n<p>After the Majlis segment, which builds consensus and bridges divides, the audience at TEDSummit and around the world voted a second time. Khanna surpassed Benjamin with 35% of the vote, yet Msimang maintained her lead with 39% of the vote. The poll will remain live on Twitter @DohaDebates for the next seven days. </p>\n<p>QF Education City university students were among the attendees in Edinburgh, and the debate was shown at Qatar National Library, where, following the conclusion of the event, a discussion was held on the pros and cons of globalization.</p>\n<p>Amjad Atallah, Managing Director, Doha Debates, said, “This program was a phenomenal success, thanks to our terrific speakers, engaged attendees and viewers around the world, and our remarkable partnership with TED. With Doha Debates quickly garnering followers in 215 nations and territories, it’s clear that people everywhere are eager for solutions-focused dialogue on the hot topics of our time – Doha Debates’ hallmark – which we will deliver for them.”</p>\n<p>The full debate and highlights can be viewed on Doha Debates’ website and social media channels, with the conversation continuing using the hashtag #DearWorld.</p>\n<p>The revitalized Doha Debates builds on the tradition of examining complex global issues, established by Doha Debates’ original launch 14 years ago, through live debates, digital videos, a TV series, blogs, and podcasts on the world’s most pressing challenges. This innovative approach includes Majlis-style conversations designed to bridge differences, build consensus, and identify solutions to urgent global issues.</p>\n<p>The next live Doha Debates program is scheduled for September 10 in Cape Town, South Africa, with the global water shortage crisis set as the debate topic.</p>"}}},{"__typename":"ContentfulModuleImageGallery","id":"77cdbff3-9c6d-5de1-866d-147aa83c6e8f","images":[{"caption":null,"image":{"id":"1f8c91dd-f3a2-5580-95a5-ab8619b8ffe9","title":"Image4 DD in Scotland","file":{"details":{"image":{"width":3830,"height":2549}}},"sizes":{"aspectRatio":1.8666666666666667,"src":"//images.ctfassets.net/2h1qowfuxkq7/4cmCPIpXpEtdcOWTd1fZoF/e2aa178376fdc6eb9f850da053c6c0b7/Image4_DD_in_Scotland.jpg?w=1120&h=600&q=85","srcSet":"//images.ctfassets.net/2h1qowfuxkq7/4cmCPIpXpEtdcOWTd1fZoF/e2aa178376fdc6eb9f850da053c6c0b7/Image4_DD_in_Scotland.jpg?w=280&h=150&q=85 280w,\n//images.ctfassets.net/2h1qowfuxkq7/4cmCPIpXpEtdcOWTd1fZoF/e2aa178376fdc6eb9f850da053c6c0b7/Image4_DD_in_Scotland.jpg?w=560&h=300&q=85 560w,\n//images.ctfassets.net/2h1q